The following example [$merge](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/merge) syntax writes the results to a
`sampleDB.mySampleData` collection on the Atlas cluster named
`myTestCluster`. The example doesn't specify a project ID; the
[$merge](manual/reference/operator/aggregation/merge) stage uses the ID of the project that contains your
federated database instance.

> **Example:**&#x20;
>
> ```json
> db.mySampleData.aggregate(
>   [
>     {
>       "$merge": {
>         "into": {
>           "atlas": {
>             "clusterName": "myTestCluster",
>             "db": "sampleDB",
>             "coll": "mySampleData"
>           }
>         },
>         ...
>       }
>     }
>   ]
> )
> ```
